Get the car.

244
00:18:02.618 --> 00:18:05.351
Look at this room. John.

245
00:18:05.905 --> 00:18:07.121
Look.

246
00:18:09.588 --> 00:18:12.250
We can be a family again.

247
00:18:12.346 --> 00:18:16.682
But you want to risk it all. disrespect
us. and for what. for vengeance?

248
00:18:16.776 --> 00:18:19.412
- He betrayed me.
- I don't care.

249
00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:21.432
He betrayed us.

250
00:18:21.717 --> 00:18:29.030
I'm sorry you...
will never understand what happens...

251
00:18:29.725 --> 00:18:32.083
when you're in prison.

252
00:18:32.176 --> 00:18:34.343
But you could go
back to pris...

253
00:18:35.217 --> 00:18:37.103
I swear to God...

254
00:18:37.568 --> 00:18:41.850
I'd rather die than go back.

255
00:18:41.997 --> 00:18:45.912
There's no going back.
never. ever again.

256
00:18:46.056 --> 00:18:48.491
Christ saved you. John.

257
00:18:48.596 --> 00:18:50.661
Don't turn your back on him.

258
00:18:50.938 --> 00:18:54.000
Don't turn your back on us.

259
00:19:02.756 --> 00:19:04.302
I...

260
00:19:15.517 --> 00:19:18.961
I don't know.
about 20 miles from Gunnison.

261
00:19:19.137 --> 00:19:21.050
He's coming; I have to go.

262
00:19:25.045 --> 00:19:28.293
- Who was that?
- Nobody. it's just my father.

263
00:19:28.386 --> 00:19:33.012
Hey. listen. Do you mind if
we stop at the next motel?

264
00:19:33.198 --> 00:19:34.461
It's only like 4:00?

265
00:19:34.558 --> 00:19:36.810
Yeah. but we've been
driving forever.

266
00:19:36.925 --> 00:19:38.691
It's cool. I'll drive.

267
00:19:38.795 --> 00:19:41.141
I really just want to stop.

268
00:19:41.287 --> 00:19:42.940
But if we get on the
road now. maybe...

269
00:19:42.977 --> 00:19:47.251
Scott. it's my car.
and I'm tired of being in it. okay?

270
00:19:48.038 --> 00:19:49.440
All right.

271
00:19:54.126 --> 00:19:57.183
Can you believe it?
Of all the players in this thing.

272
00:19:57.276 --> 00:20:00.481
it's the rat that could give
us our first collar. Come on.

273
00:20:02.108 --> 00:20:05.022
You guys need to use the can.
hold it.

274
00:20:05.128 --> 00:20:09.460
If you need to tinkle. sweet pea.
I'll watch you any time.

275
00:20:09.555 --> 00:20:10.490
Sit down.

276
00:20:12.858 --> 00:20:15.012
Hands behind your back.

277
00:20:28.866 --> 00:20:30.462
Took your time.

278
00:20:31.535 --> 00:20:35.162
It takes time to gain
a man's confidence.

279
00:20:35.717 --> 00:20:39.012
You're right.
He'll bite on anything I say.

280
00:20:39.206 --> 00:20:40.951
You just tell me
where we trap him.

281
00:20:40.985 --> 00:20:44.241
and I'll tell him that's
where the money is.

282
00:21:02.725 --> 00:21:05.880
Hey. you're the guy from
the gas station. right?

283
00:21:06.026 --> 00:21:06.672
Yeah.

284
00:21:06.816 --> 00:21:08.880
I'm the guy who was
having car trouble.

285
00:21:11.298 --> 00:21:13.692
Seems to be purring
along now. huh?

286
00:21:13.836 --> 00:21:14.723
Yeah.

287
00:21:15.276 --> 00:21:20.140
Water pump.
200 bucks for this heap.

288
00:21:20.558 --> 00:21:22.433
Well. they'll get you.

289
00:21:22.525 --> 00:21:25.160
Look. I hope I'm
not out of line.

290
00:21:25.255 --> 00:21:28.203
but I heard you telling the
cop back there about your hand.

291
00:21:28.276 --> 00:21:30.453
My old man was killed in
'Nam when I was a kid.

292
00:21:30.485 --> 00:21:33.083
and so I have the utmost
respect for our servicemen.

293
00:21:33.217 --> 00:21:36.982
- Just serving my country.
- A lot of us are grateful for it.

294
00:21:37.265 --> 00:21:39.943
Listen. if you need a
ride or something...

295
00:21:40.765 --> 00:21:43.540
Well. to be honest
with you. my...

296
00:21:43.638 --> 00:21:46.130
my dogs are kind of barking.

297
00:21:46.276 --> 00:21:49.712
Well. all right. Jerry Curtin.

298
00:21:50.178 --> 00:21:54.282
Clyde. Clyde May.

299
00:21:54.838 --> 00:21:58.650
My kid Danny's riding shotgun. I hope
you don't mind sitting in the back.

300
00:21:59.768 --> 00:22:06.430
- Hi. I'm Danielle.
- Hi. yourself.

301
00:22:16.715 --> 00:22:19.251
- Hey.
- What do you want?

302
00:22:19.535 --> 00:22:22.171
- I need to use the bathroom.
- Again?

303
00:22:22.727 --> 00:22:26.452
- I have a small bladder.
- That ain't all you got.

304
00:22:32.705 --> 00:22:33.832
Get up.

305
00:22:42.865 --> 00:22:43.891
Well?

306
00:22:44.356 --> 00:22:45.813
They plan to trap you.

307
00:22:45.955 --> 00:22:49.673
The big one-
he's got friends in Utah. Criminals.

308
00:22:49.816 --> 00:22:53.580
A town called Panguitch.
They grow drugs on the farm there.

309
00:22:53.685 --> 00:22:56.843
They'll tell you that's where
the money is. but no money.

310
00:22:56.967 --> 00:23:00.312
Just old friends with guns.
waiting for you.

311
00:23:00.448 --> 00:23:06.162
Easy enough.
We take a pass on Panguitch.

312
00:23:08.018 --> 00:23:12.873
- Where's the money really?
- I'll find out soon enough.

313
00:23:13.017 --> 00:23:16.360
But $200.000 was old price
for this information.

314
00:23:16.457 --> 00:23:21.221
- I want a new price.
- She's trying to renegotiate.

315
00:23:21.596 --> 00:23:25.651
If it wasn't for me.
you'd be face down in a marijuana farm.

316
00:23:26.397 --> 00:23:29.402
- One third.
- Ha!

317
00:23:29.547 --> 00:23:34.401
It's gonna take a lot more than information
if you want a million-six. sweet pea.

318
00:23:34.508 --> 00:23:37.511
- Such as?
- You know.

319
00:23:37.705 --> 00:23:41.142
Piece of that can
anytime I want it.

320
00:23:41.236 --> 00:23:44.252
- Is that it?
- Aren't you gonna slap me?

321
00:23:44.346 --> 00:23:47.313
I've slept with men for a lot less.
trust me.

322
00:23:47.457 --> 00:23:49.903
And what happened to
"never in a 1.000 years?"

323
00:23:50.046 --> 00:23:52.252
That was negotiating.

324
00:23:56.836 --> 00:23:58.012
So.

325
00:24:00.047 --> 00:24:01.082
Deal?

326
00:24:03.398 --> 00:24:04.520
Deal.

327
00:24:10.778 --> 00:24:13.222
We got a $150.000 here. John.

328
00:24:13.316 --> 00:24:14.780
With Vittorio's
place in Solanas.

329
00:24:14.817 --> 00:24:17.171
we'll be able to live
off the interest.

330
00:24:19.165 --> 00:24:20.621
Where's your father?

331
00:24:28.538 --> 00:24:30.421
Everything all right. boss?

332
00:24:30.557 --> 00:24:34.331
Yeah. Let's get
this over with...

333
00:24:35.586 --> 00:24:38.552
so I can get back to my family.

334
00:24:39.436 --> 00:24:43.060
She'll get it done.
Nika and I have come too far together.

335
00:24:43.157 --> 00:24:44.860
When money's on the line.
you trust no one.

336
00:24:44.897 --> 00:24:46.013
Sometimes you have to.

337
00:24:46.157 --> 00:24:48.793
Not if you want to survive.
you don't.

338
00:24:49.075 --> 00:24:51.141
You really don't trust anyone.
do you?

339
00:24:52.306 --> 00:24:55.312
Can you blame me after
all that's happened?

340
00:24:55.877 --> 00:24:59.401
No. I mean before that.
Before prison.

341
00:24:59.505 --> 00:25:01.491
Every time I trusted someone.
I got burned.

342
00:25:01.525 --> 00:25:05.530
Every time I got close to someone.
I got screwed.

343
00:25:06.686 --> 00:25:10.222
I know better.
and so should you.

344
00:25:10.415 --> 00:25:12.531
That's right. the Lotus Motel.

345
00:25:13.036 --> 00:25:16.951
I don't know the number.
I can't talk anymore; I have to go.

346
00:25:26.716 --> 00:25:27.893
Oh. check it.

347
00:25:27.985 --> 00:25:31.422
I know this might be a little
forward and all. but. um.

348
00:25:31.568 --> 00:25:34.480
let me ask you something.

349
00:25:34.626 --> 00:25:38.540
You got a man?
I mean. a boyfriend?

350
00:25:38.686 --> 00:25:40.512
No. What am I thinking?
You're Mormon...

351
00:25:40.545 --> 00:25:45.872
I'm not Mormon. You think all
girls from Utah are Mormons?

352
00:25:47.736 --> 00:25:50.083
They are. aren't they?

353
00:25:51.105 --> 00:25:55.772
Well. yo. hey.
Yo. then you can party. right? Hey.

354
00:25:57.396 --> 00:26:00.421
When I land. I want 12 armed agents
waiting for me on the ground.

355
00:26:00.457 --> 00:26:03.063
Tell them I want to go straight
to the motel from the airstrip.

356
00:26:03.097 --> 00:26:04.212
You got it.

357
00:26:08.297 --> 00:26:11.260
I was an ass before.
I apologize.

358
00:26:11.355 --> 00:26:15.452
A little bit.
It's all right. Here you go.

359
00:26:15.645 --> 00:26:18.663
- I was a huge ass.
- I apologize.

360
00:26:18.797 --> 00:26:21.102
I'm not going to
argue with you.

361
00:26:21.245 --> 00:26:25.302
Well. I mean. what were the odds
that you were actually a doctor?

362
00:26:25.396 --> 00:26:30.873
Uh. all right. fair enough.
They're probably not good. but. um...

363
00:26:31.427 --> 00:26:36.243
And I should not have interrupted you.
and I'm sorry.

364
00:26:36.377 --> 00:26:39.493
- I'm sorry. too.
- Well. then. apologies accepted.

365
00:26:39.587 --> 00:26:46.050
- I recommend the blueberry pie.
- Well. blueberry pie it is.

366
00:27:02.595 --> 00:27:05.750
- Hey. there. Danny.
- Hey.

367
00:27:06.815 --> 00:27:10.770
Sure is nice of your daddy to
buy me a room for the night.

368
00:27:10.915 --> 00:27:14.361
Yeah. he's always helping
out with vets and stuff.

369
00:27:15.145 --> 00:27:16.881
Yeah. good man.

370
00:27:17.445 --> 00:27:21.120
But I was wishing we could have
kept going on toward Utah.

371
00:27:22.675 --> 00:27:26.591
Lots of light left in the day.
lots of road to go.

372
00:27:26.735 --> 00:27:29.563
When Dad's back acts up.
we stop.

373
00:27:31.735 --> 00:27:35.933
Young Miss?
That's kind of insulting. isn't it?

374
00:27:36.357 --> 00:27:36.953
Hmm?

375
00:27:37.096 --> 00:27:40.252
I mean. you're a grown woman.

376
00:27:41.226 --> 00:27:45.902
But adults are always trying
to infantilize girls your age.

377
00:27:46.085 --> 00:27:48.060
treat you like children.

378
00:27:48.198 --> 00:27:51.643
No duh. My dad won't let me
get earrings. and I'm 14.

379
00:27:51.786 --> 00:27:53.610
You see?
That's what I'm saying.

380
00:27:53.755 --> 00:27:56.442
You are more than
perfectly capable of. uh...

381
00:27:56.537 --> 00:27:58.990
- of making your own decisions...
- Tell my dad that.

382
00:27:59.027 --> 00:28:01.993
Yeah. but he won't want
to hear it. right?

383
00:28:02.177 --> 00:28:08.533
Because he wants to keep
you as a baby. Right?

384
00:28:08.628 --> 00:28:13.011
Even though you're...
you're more than old enough to

385
00:28:13.155 --> 00:28:20.470
to choose how you want to-to dress.
or. uh. accessorize.

386
00:28:20.807 --> 00:28:22.162
What are you doing?

387
00:28:22.306 --> 00:28:24.103
Just in need of a friend.
that's all...

388
00:28:24.136 --> 00:28:26.251
No. No. I'm telling my dad.

389
00:28:26.397 --> 00:28:27.183
Wait!

390
00:28:34.045 --> 00:28:36.251
She's got it all wrong.

391
00:28:37.087 --> 00:28:38.783
Go wait outside.

392
00:28:49.017 --> 00:28:51.510
You and I are gonna
work this out.

393
00:28:52.206 --> 00:28:56.832
Jerry... you really
don't want to do this.

394
00:28:59.848 --> 00:29:04.232
Thing I like about you
is your determination.

395
00:29:04.696 --> 00:29:09.512
I've got family in Kladno that have
been waiting for me to send for them.

396
00:29:09.608 --> 00:29:11.761
They know what kind
of work you're in?

397
00:29:13.296 --> 00:29:15.741
They think I work
at Starbuck's.

398
00:29:15.937 --> 00:29:18.712
Mmm. Mmm.

399
00:29:24.366 --> 00:29:27.001
How stupid do you think I am?

400
00:29:35.985 --> 00:29:38.482
My daddy always said.
"Fool me once. shame on you.

401
00:29:38.528 --> 00:29:41.760
Fool me twice.
and I put you in the ground. "

402
00:29:42.085 --> 00:29:46.093
Any more games.
and I stop the hooker's air. understand?

403
00:29:52.797 --> 00:29:54.911
Thanks for the dance.
sweet pea.

404
00:29:59.966 --> 00:30:03.642
- You bitch!
- Fooled you.

405
00:30:09.168 --> 00:30:12.181
I carried it;
the cons can change it.

406
00:30:13.157 --> 00:30:16.411
Oh. you really suck.
Bellick. you know that?

407
00:30:16.508 --> 00:30:19.091
- Roll 'em.
- Let's go.

408
00:30:23.157 --> 00:30:24.750
Put your hands
behind your back.

409
00:30:29.575 --> 00:30:30.842
Thank you.

410
00:30:30.975 --> 00:30:33.471
You're as stupid as the prison doc.
you know that?

411
00:30:33.518 --> 00:30:34.691
Ignore him.

412
00:30:34.837 --> 00:30:37.670
He conned her. too. Made her think
he loved her. and look what she got.

413
00:30:37.708 --> 00:30:40.913
An overdose and a shot
at 30 years inside.

414
00:30:43.556 --> 00:30:45.523
What are you talking about?

415
00:30:45.668 --> 00:30:48.550
Guess you haven't been reading
the papers. have you. college boy?

416
00:30:48.586 --> 00:30:49.980
Cops found your girlfriend-

417
00:30:50.136 --> 00:30:53.802
fish-belly white.
garglin' her own puke.

418
00:30:53.948 --> 00:30:54.913
Shut up.

419
00:30:55.055 --> 00:30:58.211
But what do you care. a long as
she left the door open for you?

420
00:30:58.305 --> 00:31:01.692
- Shut up!
- Hit a spot. didn't I?

421
00:31:15.136 --> 00:31:16.572
Dad...

422
00:31:30.425 --> 00:31:33.391
It really is like the
best pie I've ever had.

423
00:31:33.945 --> 00:31:35.540
You know what it
needs though...

424
00:31:35.597 --> 00:31:37.660
- Hmm?
- Some crack.

425
00:31:38.687 --> 00:31:41.412
No. I mean. you know. not a lot.
A pinch.

426
00:31:41.555 --> 00:31:43.530
- A pinch of crack?
- A pinch of crack.

427
00:31:43.666 --> 00:31:46.920
A pinch of crack.
a dollop of smack. Mm.

428
00:31:47.017 --> 00:31:50.033
- That's good pie.
- That's so wrong.

429
00:31:50.177 --> 00:31:50.913
No?

430
00:31:53.377 --> 00:31:54.403
I'm sorry.

431
00:31:58.988 --> 00:31:59.780
Hello.

432
00:31:59.878 --> 00:32:05.630
- Sara... it's me.
- What do you want?

433
00:32:06.375 --> 00:32:08.301
I don't have time to talk.

434
00:32:08.907 --> 00:32:11.892
And there's every chance they're
listening to this call right now.

435
00:32:11.926 --> 00:32:13.942
but there's a lot
I want to say.

436
00:32:14.398 --> 00:32:16.412
Please don't hang up on me.

437
00:32:16.508 --> 00:32:18.580
I don't...
I don't want talk to you.

438
00:32:18.677 --> 00:32:20.983
I heard about...

439
00:32:22.305 --> 00:32:24.472
I heard about what happened.

440
00:32:27.015 --> 00:32:29.651
I want you to know that...

441
00:32:29.745 --> 00:32:32.603
I want you to know
how sorry I am...

442
00:32:32.656 --> 00:32:33.871
for everything.

443
00:32:34.005 --> 00:32:36.191
Sorry's not going to do
me a whole lot of good

444
00:32:36.226 --> 00:32:38.382
with what I'm up
against right now.

445
00:32:38.526 --> 00:32:45.132
Listen... anyone with any ties to
me and my brother is in danger now.

446
00:32:45.237 --> 00:32:48.721
I have no ties to you
and your brother anymore.

447
00:32:48.856 --> 00:32:52.442
There is a way I
can protect you.

448
00:32:52.728 --> 00:32:55.173
It's already in
your possession.

449
00:32:55.355 --> 00:32:57.183
What are you talking about.

450
00:32:57.287 --> 00:33:01.103
It was real. Sara.
You and me...

451
00:33:02.028 --> 00:33:04.623
It's real.

452
00:33:09.118 --> 00:33:10.141
Michael? I...

453
00:33:11.818 --> 00:33:13.250
Michael?

454
00:33:21.038 --> 00:33:22.721
How long to the motel?

455
00:33:22.867 --> 00:33:24.601
Approximately ten minutes. sir.

456
00:33:24.696 --> 00:33:26.291
Let's make it five?

457
00:33:32.456 --> 00:33:36.793
Ooh. Yo. I haven't taken a
shower like that in forever!

458
00:33:38.327 --> 00:33:41.391
- Where are you going?
- I was going to surprise you.

459
00:33:41.526 --> 00:33:42.983
Surprise me how?

460
00:33:43.106 --> 00:33:45.153
I was going to get
some tequila and lime.

461
00:33:45.178 --> 00:33:46.480
All right. well. hold up-

462
00:33:46.587 --> 00:33:51.531
No. no. No. it'll only take a minute.
Stay here and relax.

463
00:33:51.726 --> 00:33:53.362
You seem kind of nervous.

464
00:33:53.466 --> 00:33:57.230
- I do?
- Yeah. you're sweating.

465
00:33:57.326 --> 00:33:58.971
Maybe I am nervous.

466
00:33:59.115 --> 00:34:02.501
Trust me. girl. you got nothing
to worry about. all right?

467
00:34:02.647 --> 00:34:07.132
- I'm one of the good guys.
- You seem like it.

468
00:34:44.196 --> 00:34:45.503
Hang on tight.

469
00:34:45.647 --> 00:34:48.233
I had the manager unlock
the door. Gotcha.

470
00:35:28.997 --> 00:35:31.673
If you're looking
for the rat. John...

471
00:35:32.146 --> 00:35:34.921
Fibonacci's 2.000
miles from here.

472
00:35:38.487 --> 00:35:40.231
Who are you?

473
00:35:41.158 --> 00:35:43.033
Local cops or Feds?

474
00:35:43.688 --> 00:35:47.551
Feds. John. only roll out the
best for a man of your stature.

475
00:35:51.265 --> 00:35:54.081
I deserve to know
who turned on me.

476
00:35:54.225 --> 00:35:55.493
Tony?

477
00:35:56.185 --> 00:35:58.783
The man was facing RICO rap.

478
00:35:59.567 --> 00:36:02.111
He did not want to to prison.

479
00:36:02.257 --> 00:36:06.820
I'm sure can appreciate that. knowing
what you know about the place now.

480
00:36:07.158 --> 00:36:10.972
Whatever you're thinking
about doing John...

481
00:36:11.097 --> 00:36:12.173
don't.

482
00:36:16.528 --> 00:36:18.971
You are going back
to Fox River today

483
00:36:19.117 --> 00:36:21.943
or the morgue.
that's your call.

484
00:36:27.798 --> 00:36:28.870
Coming out.

485
00:36:29.568 --> 00:36:31.491
Weapons come out first. John.

486
00:36:33.348 --> 00:36:34.420
Forgive me.

487
00:36:38.596 --> 00:36:42.221
Yeah. I'm coming out.

488
00:36:44.957 --> 00:36:48.403
Easy. John. Easy.

489
00:36:50.148 --> 00:36:51.781
We got a weapon. right hand.

490
00:36:51.926 --> 00:36:53.803
These are serious men here.

491
00:36:53.925 --> 00:36:56.721
They have instructions to shoot
at the first sign of aggression.

492
00:36:56.758 --> 00:36:59.440
Please. I'm asking
you. respectfully.

493
00:36:59.588 --> 00:37:04.582
drop the weapon.
kneel and put your hands on your head.

494
00:37:06.397 --> 00:37:09.691
I kneel only to God.

495
00:37:10.615 --> 00:37:13.023
I don't see Him here.

496
00:37:19.087 --> 00:37:19.932
John!

497
00:37:48.246 --> 00:37:51.831
I think I screwed up.
My dad's an Air Force colonel.

498
00:37:52.346 --> 00:37:56.732
Total Nazi. One of those...
nightmare overprotective dads.

499
00:37:56.916 --> 00:37:59.130
Mmm-hmm. Yeah?

500
00:37:59.227 --> 00:38:00.582
Well. I called him.

501
00:38:01.325 --> 00:38:05.002
Told him I was
traveling with you.

502
00:38:05.145 --> 00:38:08.391
I told him that we were
staying in the same hotel room.

503
00:38:10.576 --> 00:38:12.690
- Girl.
- What?

504
00:38:13.298 --> 00:38:15.942
You got to learn how to lie. girl.
What you thinking?

505
00:38:15.966 --> 00:38:20.580
I don't... Yeah. I-
for some reason I don't know how.

506
00:38:20.678 --> 00:38:24.501
He was mad enough when I told him I
was staying in a hotel room with a guy.

507
00:38:24.638 --> 00:38:26.091
that was one thing...

508
00:38:26.238 --> 00:38:26.832
Yeah. yeah.

509
00:38:26.936 --> 00:38:30.092
But when I told him I was staying
in a hotel with a guy that...

510
00:38:30.275 --> 00:38:32.483
I maybe sort of liked...

511
00:38:32.677 --> 00:38:33.891
he lost it.

512
00:38:37.836 --> 00:38:38.860
Wait.

513
00:38:39.366 --> 00:38:43.422
- Wait. what?
- Is that okay?

514
00:38:56.825 --> 00:38:59.423
At least let us
take you into town.

515
00:39:00.297 --> 00:39:01.331
No.

516
00:39:01.975 --> 00:39:05.283
If I'm seen with you.
it's a lot of trouble for me.

517
00:39:05.556 --> 00:39:07.583
I can walk; it's only a mile.

518
00:39:07.678 --> 00:39:10.450
We never would've made
it this far without you.

519
00:39:10.595 --> 00:39:12.662
But now you're
crossing the border...

520
00:39:13.125 --> 00:39:14.670
without me.

521
00:39:14.815 --> 00:39:19.633
You can't go where we're going.
It's not a life for you.

522
00:39:22.876 --> 00:39:27.883
Then that's it then.
It's over for good.

523
00:39:29.037 --> 00:39:30.542
Thank you.

524
00:39:32.297 --> 00:39:33.470
Be safe.

525
00:39:40.606 --> 00:39:41.822
Good luck.

526
00:39:49.096 --> 00:39:51.780
I loved you. Michael.

527
00:39:52.068 --> 00:39:55.602
And I thought I was going to get
that back. but you just used me.

528
00:39:55.695 --> 00:39:56.771
That's not true.

529
00:39:56.955 --> 00:39:58.883
I deserve more than this.

530
00:39:59.025 --> 00:40:02.703
I deserve more than just being the
girl you call when you need something.

531
00:40:02.846 --> 00:40:04.902
You really think you're
gonna find the money in Utah?

532
00:40:04.938 --> 00:40:07.863
I don't care about
the money in Utah!

533
00:40:08.285 --> 00:40:10.582
I don't want any more crime.

534
00:40:10.866 --> 00:40:16.722
I turn you in. I get $200.000.
Legal money.

535
00:40:22.006 --> 00:40:24.121
You're the policemen's
problem now.

536
00:40:24.258 --> 00:40:25.290
Nika...

537
00:40:25.387 --> 00:40:27.971
Don't come any closer
or I'll shoot you!

538
00:40:28.388 --> 00:40:29.980
No. you won't.

539
00:40:58.797 --> 00:41:00.532
Good luck to you.

540
00:41:26.848 --> 00:41:28.153
- Hey.
- Hey.

541
00:41:28.345 --> 00:41:32.681
Um. HQ called. They're asking
why you didn't intercept Abruzzi

542
00:41:32.867 --> 00:41:35.081
when he was walking
towards the motel.

543
00:41:35.316 --> 00:41:38.730
The man was a mob boss.
The right move was to get him trapped.

544
00:41:38.857 --> 00:41:42.403
They're saying the way you played it.
there was only one possible outcome.

545
00:41:42.437 --> 00:41:44.211
HQ has a problem with
the way I do things.

546
00:41:44.247 --> 00:41:47.742
they can pick up a gun and follow
me into the field next time.

547
00:41:53.537 --> 00:41:57.350
Scofield always knew the
rat was the key to Abruzzi.

548
00:41:57.497 --> 00:42:00.790
We just put it out on
the wire and Abruzzi bit.

549
00:42:09.458 --> 00:42:11.382
Speaking of Scofield...

550
00:42:11.617 --> 00:42:13.871
That crash was staged.

551
00:42:20.645 --> 00:42:22.852
Pig blood.

552
00:42:24.148 --> 00:42:25.633
Smart kid.

553
00:42:31.248 --> 00:42:32.881
The problem with...

554
00:42:33.216 --> 00:42:36.272
being that clever is
that sooner or later.

555
00:42:36.416 --> 00:42:39.241
you end up getting too
clever for your own good.

556
00:42:44.568 --> 00:42:45.742
Good night.

557
00:43:10.346 --> 00:43:12.880
You have no idea
what you're in for.

558
00:43:13.305 --> 00:44:13.636
